You can change your cookie settings at any time. </p>

            <script type="text/javascript">
                $(document).ready(function () {
                    //let's check cookie to see if the user has dismissed it in the past..
                    //if they have no need to tell them again.
                    //Need to be careful if we change this. as we may need to manually delete the cookie ourselves in the future.
                    //we can do this using the line below. just set the expiry date to one in the past!
                    //document.cookie = "myAccPrivacyClosed; expires = Thu, 18 Dec 1092 12:00:00 UTC; path=/";

                    //user has told us to dismiss, we don't want to keep bugging them!
                    if (document.cookie.indexOf('myAccPrivacyClosed') > -1) {
                        $('#PrivacyPolicyNotification').hide();
                    }
                })

                function closeDiv() {
                    //let's get todays date and make sure the expiry of the cookies doesn't take place for a couple of months.
                    var CurrentDate = new Date();
                    CurrentDate.setMonth(CurrentDate.getMonth() + 18);

                    //user has told us to dismiss, we don't want to keep bugging them!
                    document.cookie = "myAccPrivacyClosed; expires = " + CurrentDate + "; path=/";
                    $('#PrivacyPolicyNotification').hide();
                }
